hnormal\">a</span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">)</span></span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.23em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"frac-line\" style=\"border-bottom-width:0.04em;\"></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.677em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">asinh</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\"><span class=\"mopen delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">y</span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">a</span><span class=\"mclose delimcenter\" style=\"top:0em;\">)</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.936em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose nulldelimiter\"></span></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span></span></span></span></span>","key":"ecd6iCCBaz"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":85,"column":1},"end":{"line":85,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"where ","position":{"start":{"line":85,"column":1},"end":{"line":85,"column":1}},"key":"vX1MaweD0a"},{"type":"inlineMath","value":"a","position":{"start":{"line":85,"column":1},"end":{"line":85,"column":1}},"html":"<span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>a</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">a</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">a</span></span></span></span>","key":"Wyz8LjXqbo"},{"type":"text","value":" is a parameter that controls the transition between linear and logarithmic behavior. The ","position":{"start":{"line":85,"column":1},"end":{"line":85,"column":1}},"key":"oRKqU4Fmxp"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"Makie.AsinhScale","position":{"start":{"line":85,"column":1},"end":{"line":85,"column":1}},"key":"eN6aOSTVsX"},{"type":"text","value":" constructor takes this parameter as an argument.","position":{"start":{"line":85,"column":1},"end":{"line":85,"column":1}},"key":"bCoXasXsg0"}],"key":"Rd04UCHQLZ"}],"icon":false,"class":"dropdown","key":"aom8GEEEhg"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":88,"column":1},"end":{"line":88,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Program 27","position":{"start":{"line":88,"column":1},"end":{"line":88,"column":1}},"key":"nnEC8p7kSV"}],"identifier":"program-27","label":"Program 27","html_id":"program-27","implicit":true,"key":"tBbAFkd5zh"},{"type":"include","file":"SpectralMethodsTrefethen/src/scripts/p27.jl","literal":true,"children":[{"type":"code","value":"using CairoMakie, LaTeXStrings, FFTW\n\"\"\"\np27 - Solve KdV eq. u_t + u u_x + u_xxx = 0 on [-π, π] by\n        FFT with integrating factor v = exp(-ik³t) * û.\n\"\"\"\nfunction p27(N=256, tmax=0.006, Δt=0.4/N^2)\n    @assert iseven(N) \"Must choose an even value of N\"\n    # Set up grid and two-soliton initial data:\n    x = (2π / N) * (-N/2:N/2-1)\n    soliton(x, a) = 3a^2 * sech(0.5 * a * x)^2\n    u = @. soliton(x + 2, 25) + soliton(x + 1, 16)\n\n    # Set up time stepping:\n    tplot = tmax / 80\n    plotgap = round(Int, tplot / Δt)\n    Δt = tplot / plotgap\n    ntime = round(Int, tmax / Δt)\n\n    # Find integrating factor and solve PDE:\n    k = [0:N/2-1; 0]\n    ik³ = 1im * k .^ 3\n    g = -0.5im * Δt * k\n    E = exp.(Δt * ik³ / 2)\n    E² = E .^ 2\n    û = rfft(u)\n    udata = u\n    tdata = [0.0]\n    for n = 1:ntime\n        t = n * Δt\n        a = g .* rfft(irfft(û, N) .^ 2)\n        b = g .* rfft(irfft(E .* (û + a / 2), N) .^ 2)    # 4th-order...\n        c = g .* rfft(irfft(E .* û + b / 2, N) .^ 2)      # ...Runge–Kutta\n        d = g .* rfft(irfft(E² .* û + E .* c, N) .^ 2)\n        û = @. E² * û + (E² * a + 2 * E * (b + c) + d) / 6\n        if iszero(rem(n, plotgap))\n            u = irfft(û, N)\n            udata = [udata u]\n            tdata = [tdata; t]\n        end\n    end\n    return heatmap(x, tdata, udata; colormap=:Blues, interpolate=true,\n        axis=(xlabel=L\"x\", ylabel=L\"t\"))\nend","lang":"julia","showLineNumbers":true,"label":"p27","identifier":"p27","filename":"p27","html_id":"p27","key":"RmmGtNGQ8f"}],"key":"V2KzoKgNnk"},{"type":"heading","depth":3,"position":{"start":{"line":97,"column":1},"end":{"line":97,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Output 27","position":{"start":{"line":97,"column":1},"end":{"line":97,"column":1}},"key":"CjHkLXjrOl"}],"identifier":"output-27","label":"Output 27","html_id":"output-27","implicit":true,"key":"Rx9LsSAWkI"}],"key":"nfWOpZE1Km"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-code","children":[{"type":"code","lang":"julia","executable":true,"value":"p27()","identifier":"output27-code","html_id":"output27-code","key":"Xc9BG58BjU"},{"type":"outputs","id":"6L7Hy80aqw01-0xAFqBVu","children":[{"type":"output","children":[],"jupyter_data":{"output_type":"execute_result","execution_count":5,"metadata":{},"data":{"image/png":{"content_type":"image/png","hash":"07453f68b9583fb491a8243e362a92c2","path":"https://tobydriscoll.net/build/07453f68b9583fb491a8243e362a92c2.png"},"text/html":{"content_type":"text/html","hash":"08e5214118c0ea1d3da6483e7a1854a2","path":"https://tobydriscoll.net/build/08e5214118c0ea1d3da6483e7a1854a2.html"}}},"identifier":"output27-outputs-0","html_id":"output27-outputs-0","key":"XYjqUjoX0J"}],"identifier":"output27-outputs","html_id":"output27-outputs","key":"aKV7RiTlvr"}],"label":"output27","identifier":"output27","html_id":"output27","key":"Elad6YkV2R"},{"type":"block","children":[{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":104,"column":1},"end":{"line":104,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The heatmap in this case shows clearly the way the humps emerge from their interaction shifted from their original characteristic paths. That’s a nonlinear effect in KdV.","position":{"start":{"line":104,"column":1},"end":{"line":104,"column":1}},"key":"OhhBDdHsI1"}],"key":"FWSB3YMv7X"},{"type":"admonition","kind":"note","children":[{"type":"admonitionTitle","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Real ","key":"Uj5e694hNg"},{"type":"abbreviation","title":"fast Fourier transform","children":[{"type":"text","value":"FFT","key":"KSuRA2WeJC"}],"key":"uoWGP6R7Kp"}],"key":"YaQI7Ovoli"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":109,"column":1},"end":{"line":109,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Because we use ","position":{"start":{"line":109,"column":1},"end":{"line":109,"column":1}},"key":"NgzTiBFJPB"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"rfft","position":{"start":{"line":109,"column":1},"end":{"line":109,"column":1}},"key":"Qnyenrqvpa"},{"type":"text","value":" and ","position":{"start":{"line":109,"column":1},"end":{"line":109,"column":1}},"key":"qyMKkk1Dra"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"irfft","position":{"start":{"line":109,"column":1},"end":{"line":109,"column":1}},"key":"TdHlRVFoIw"},{"type":"text","value":" for the Fourier transforms, we never have to explictly take the real part of the results, and we enjoy a factor of 2 speedup over a generic ","key":"IjNzW0qQXC"},{"type":"abbreviation","title":"fast Fourier transform","children":[{"type":"text","value":"FFT","key":"UKvtnU34Ct"}],"key":"qEg3DcFa3W"},{"type":"text","value":".","key":"ViTTRQcIcc"}],"key":"ob0rChR41p"}],"icon":false,"class":"dropdown","key":"eqewr4cj87"},{"type":"admonition","kind":"note","children":[{"type":"admonitionTitle","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Interpolated heatmap","position":{"start":{"line":112,"column":1},"end":{"line":112,"column":1}},"key":"ZygKB7uY3P"}],"key":"n2ixgpHyo8"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":115,"column":1},"end":{"line":115,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I used ","position":{"start":{"line":115,"column":1},"end":{"line":115,"column":1}},"key":"FCiVBXhmcK"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"interpolate=true","position":{"start":{"line":115,"column":1},"end":{"line":115,"column":1}},"key":"GInfBjoItD"},{"type":"text","value":" in the ","position":{"start":{"line":115,"column":1},"end":{"line":115,"column":1}},"key":"kuaAJY3dFi"},{"type":"inlineCode","value":"heatmap","position":{"start":{"line":115,"column":1},"end":{"line":115,"column":1}},"key":"htavtzRJip"},{"type":"text","value":" call to get a smoother-looking plot. I guess that’s a bit hypocritical given my earlier stances on keeping spectral accuracy, but interpolating faithfully to 4th order in time is not easy here.","position":{"start":{"line":115,"column":1},"end":{"line":115,"column":1}},"key":"k7aNPRMqj3"}],"key":"li4Ixz41r5"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":117,"column":1},"end":{"line":117,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Simple fixed-time-step implementations of methods for ","key":"nPc8iOe140"},{"type":"abbreviation","title":"initial-value problem","children":[{"type":"text","value":"IVP","key":"oyo6KbWY8M"}],"key":"Z9nIzEOSmQ"},{"type":"text","value":"s are great to learn from, but they should not be used when solving challenging problems. Julia has the best collection of ","key":"ojfYhiCabD"},{"type":"abbreviation","title":"initial-value problem","children":[{"type":"text","value":"IVP","key":"E0LWREdJAT"}],"key":"FmdzZ19PWC"},{"type":"text","value":" solvers in the world, in the ","key":"qMW1RN6VvP"},{"type":"link","url":"https://docs.sciml.ai/DiffEqDocs/stable/","position":{"start":{"line":117,"column":1},"end":{"line":117,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"DifferentialEquations","position":{"start":{"line":117,"column":1},"end":{"line":117,"column":1}},"key":"pZFkTPdczw"}],"urlSource":"https://docs.sciml.ai/DiffEqDocs/stable/","key":"RlHhro1vY7"},{"type":"text","value":" package. Most of its sovlers automatically provide adaptive step size and interpolation in time. The package even offers ","position":{"start":{"line":117,"column":1},"end":{"line":117,"column":1}},"key":"hkUZ7MCiua"},{"type":"link","url":"https://docs.sciml.ai/DiffEqDocs/stable/solvers/ode_solve/#exp_RK","position":{"start":{"line":117,"column":1},"end":{"line":117,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"exponential Runge–Kutta methods","position":{"start":{"line":117,"column":1},"end":{"line":117,"column":1}},"key":"FaimImGrvP"}],"urlSource":"https://docs.sciml.ai/DiffEqDocs/stable/solvers/ode_solve/#exp_RK","key":"atQM8nX1QL"},{"type":"text","value":" ready to use.","position":{"start":{"line":117,"column":1},"end":{"line":117,"column":1}},"key":"TXLRv3dp3U"}],"key":"mfoSm00Ydt"}],"icon":false,"class":"dropdown","key":"lMblQHq42z"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":120,"column":1},"end":{"line":120,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Program 27-anim","position":{"start":{"line":120,"column":1},"end":{"line":120,"column":1}},"key":"FW3V3adq46"}],"identifier":"program-27-anim","label":"Program 27-anim","html_id":"program-27-anim","implicit":true,"key":"iqg7YRuGd3"},{"type":"include","file":"SpectralMethodsTrefethen/src/scripts/p27anim.jl","literal":true,"children":[{"type":"code","value":"using CairoMakie, LaTeXStrings, Printf, FFTW\n\"\"\"\np27anim - Solve KdV eq. u_t + u u_x + u_xxx = 0 on [-π, π] by\n        FFT with integrating factor v = exp(-ik³t) * û.\n\"\"\"\nfunction p27anim(N=256, tmax=0.006, Δt=0.4/N^2)\n    @assert iseven(N) \"Must choose an even value of N\"\n    # Set up grid and two-soliton initial data:\n    x = (2π / N) * (-N/2:N/2-1)\n    soliton(x, a) = 3a^2 * sech(0.5 * a * x)^2\n    u = @. soliton(x + 2, 25) + soliton(x + 1, 16)\n\n    # Set up time stepping:\n    tplot = tmax / 150\n    plotgap = ceil(Int, tplot / Δt)\n    Δt = tplot / plotgap\n    ntime = round(Int, tmax / Δt)\n\n    # Find integrating factor and solve PDE:\n    k = [0:N/2-1; 0]\n    ik³ = 1im * k .^ 3\n    g = -0.5im * Δt * k\n    E = exp.(Δt * ik³ / 2)\n    E² = E .^ 2\n    time = Observable(0.0)\n    title = @lift @sprintf(\"t = %0.2e\", $time)\n    û = rfft(u)\n    u = Observable(u)\n    fig = lines(x, u;\n        axis=(; xlabel=L\"x\", xticks=MultiplesTicks(5, π, \"π\"), title))\n    anim = record(fig, \"p27anim-$N-$(1000tmax).mp4\"; framerate=30) do io\n        recordframe!(io)\n        for n in 1:ntime\n            a = g .* rfft(irfft(û, N) .^ 2)\n            b = g .* rfft(irfft(E .* (û + a / 2), N) .^ 2)    # 4th-order...\n            c = g .* rfft(irfft(E .* û + b / 2, N) .^ 2)      # ...Runge–Kutta\n            d = g .* rfft(irfft(E² .* û + E .* c, N) .^ 2)\n            û = @. E² * û + (E² * a + 2 * E * (b + c) + d) / 6\n            if iszero(rem(n, plotgap))\n                u[] = irfft(û, N)\n                time[] = n * Δt\n                recordframe!(io)\n            end\n        end\n    end\n    return anim\nend\n","lang":"julia","showLineNumbers":true,"label":"p27anim","identifier":"p27anim","filename":"p27anim","html_id":"p27anim","key":"zhvFml5utX"}],"key":"hOtcG8qc1N"},{"type":"heading","depth":3,"position":{"start":{"line":129,"column":1},"end":{"line":129,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Output 27-anim","position":{"start":{"line":129,"column":1},"end":{"line":129,"column":1}},"key":"UttdMBFS9z"}],"identifier":"output-27-anim","label":"Output 27-anim","html_id":"output-27-anim","implicit":true,"key":"ABo34dEZ3A"}],"key":"tadUMTEiyM"},{"type":"block","kind":"notebook-code","children":[{"type":"code","lang":"julia","executable":true,"value":"p27anim()","identifier":"output27anim-code","visibility":"show","html_id":"output27anim-code","key":"p9uqoNW1xK"},{"type":"outputs","id":"kf5ZkP4ZIXICSukI6EkLn","children":[{"type":"output","children":[],"jupyter_data":{"output_type":"execute_result","data":{"text/plain":"\"p27anim-256-6.0.mp4\""},"metadata":{},"execution_c